title: Can no longer launch with old launcher
body:
Hey guys,

Been using the new Alpha client today, testing the waters and reporting back a few bugs on it.  Even though its an alpha seems fairly stable atm. In the alpha we all know ranked play is disabled :( so i wanted to launch my old client, but i can no longer do so.

It goes through the calculating differences stages, and then throws an "Update failed : Unspecified error occurred. Please check the logs for more information."

Scrolling down to the bottom of the LoLPatcher.Log I am getting;

000090.401|   OKAY| DisplayError: title_error_update_failed.
000090.401|   OKAY| OnTaskComplete: 0.
000090.401|   OKAY| SetTaskState: 0.
000090.401|   OKAY| SetTroubleshootResult: .
000090.401|   OKAY| DisplayError: title_error_update_completed_in_failure.
000090.402|  ERROR| Riot::LoLLauncherLib::ThreadedPatcherWorker<struct Riot::LoLLauncherLib::UpdateResult>::HandleUpdate: c:/jenkins/workspace/rads-code-win-release/code/solutions/riotrads/source/rads/lolpatcherlib/PatcherWorker.inl(75): Worker update failed (RIOT_HRESULT=80004005, complete=yes)

I've had this issue with patch 6.8 and i had to wait until 6.9 came out to fix it :( 

If someone has a quick fix ill give it a shot, other wise ill try some more trouble shooting later.

replies.body: Never mind about this. I remembered that i recently had a copy backed up, and i reverted to that, 400~mb patch was much quicker and working fine now.

> [{quoted}](name=LiL Batman,realm=NA,application-id=2E4zVIwd,discussion-id=fpcJFj0c,comment-id=0000000000000000000000000000,timestamp=2016-05-20T17:52:57.231+0000)
>
> I'm glad to hear that you were able to get it resolved. Happy testing!

I am glad that my posts where completely over looked. Too hard basket?

Well I've spent a few hours working on this and i am making some progress on this one, 

It seems the logs are throwing back an MD5 Hash error in the "Riot Games/League of Legends/RADS/projects/lol_air_client/releases/0.0.1.201/releasemanifest". Deleting that file and re-downloading it didn't seem to help, but make the error appear quicker on the launch of the launcher.

I am going to assume that it is possible that something somewhere in that folder is cactus. Ive had enough time and patience so i deleted the entire 0.0.1.201 folder and now the launcher is re-downloading the contents.. yay 1.85gb download.. Australian internet.. it would be faster to mail the folder to me on an USB. I am hoping this resolves the issue.

Either way Ill let you know.

I really appreciate the lack of support so far. 

Ill let you know that if re-downloading that folder works. If it does not which i suspect might be possible, ill have to wait until the next patch release, in that case i am going to be rather annoyed..

Im also experiencing this issue, opened the old client and after i installed the alpha i closed it and went into alpha, then wanted to play ranked with a friend but can no longer open the old launcher.

Hey @zeebie and @zemian

Would you be able to share your logs with me? Either through Google Drive, Dropbox or Pastebin (http://pastebin.com/)

Were you guys switching between regions or doing anything outside of the normal flow? Normal flow would be something along the lines of: Launch League Client log in, interact with client, maybe get into a game, log out, launch League of Legends.

Just trying to narrow down what might be causing the issue so I can try to reproduce it but if you send me your logs I can get a better picture of the problem you guys are experiencing. Logs are located here: C:\Riot Games\League of Legends\Logs\LeagueClient Logs 

Just send the LeagueClient.log (not UX) but the more logs you can send me, the better! If you choose to use pastebin, please copy/paste the name of the log file into the title section. Thanks!

Hey

After i installed the alpha I logged on to the client, then my friends asked if i wanted to play ranked, i closed the client and tried to open the old launcher but nothing happened except for the League of Legends logo in the middel of the screen for a sec. i didnt change any settings.

I can still open the Alpha launcher and client.

Logs:
http://pastebin.com/V7iRggbc
http://pastebin.com/ZWNAYxpr
http://pastebin.com/2BpaUVYd
This was too big for pastebin https://drive.google.com/open?id=0By3frpW4xzj1alRUenJFWmVxZXc
Thanks I will take a look now!

I derped and forgot to ask for your LoLPatcher logs as well since that's where the error would actually show up.  Those are located here: C:\Riot Games\League of Legends\Logs\Patcher Logs (again, no need to send UX logs)

I solved tre problem, for some reason Avast quarantined the lol launcher after I launched the alpha client.

But thanks for taking a look at it.
I'm glad to hear that you were able to get it resolved. Happy testing!

Hello LiL Batman and Riot Venia.

Being the weekend i was having family time all day today and took the misses out to dinner only just got home.

Just wanted to confirm the following, I have not done anything out of the normal.

Step1. install alpha.
Step2. use alpha want to play ranked close Alpha
Step3. Go to launch normal client

Error Occurs.

Unlike Zemian, I dont have Avast or even Ad-Aware that could of black listed the process.

Okay ill confirm a few details.

System Details taken from a quick dxdiag.
http://pastebin.com/d1bh1P8A

Lol Client Log
http://pastebin.com/cWD2wzq6

Lol Patcher Log
http://pastebin.com/pnCZwnND

I have deleted the lol_launcher & Lol_Patcher folders inside the RADS/Projects folder and forced it to re-download the launcher and the same error is occurring.

I hope the Logs help find out whats going on. I really want to play a game so i going to use the Alpha client for now. Tbh Id love it if there was ranked enabled in the Alpha *wink* *wink* *nudge* *nudge*

Cheers

Zeebie.

Hi Zeebie and Zemian!

What operating system are you guys on? Also, how much free disk space do you have on your hard drive?

Also, generating a system  report would be extremely helpful.

You can do this in Windows by opening run window (Windows+R) and typing `dxdiag`. After that, click the Save All Information and upload that for us.

On OS X, you hit the Apple menu in the top right, click About This Mac, click System Report, File -> Save. 

Cheers!
Riot Venia
Patcher Team
